The :attr:`Alarm.uid <icalendar.cal.alarm.Alarm.uid>` accessor now falls back to vendor-specific UID properties (the existing ``X-ALARMUID`` and the newly added ``X-EVOLUTION-ALARM-UID``) when no canonical ``UID`` is present, so alarms exported by Evolution/GNOME Calendar expose a usable identifier. ``single_string_property`` now accepts an ordered list of fallback keys so further vendor aliases can be added later. AI disclosure: I used GPT-5 Codex (via the Codex CLI) to draft and refine this change and its tests; I reviewed and validated the output locally. @mvanhorn
